                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9315 Manchuria/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 3, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Information received by the Department indicates that in some Soviet circles
                    there is an uneasy feeling that the outbreak of a conflict between Japan and the
                    Soviet Union in the spring or summer of this year is within the realm of
                    possibility.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
